description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking an an enthusiastic Practice Nurse to join our team. You will be supported by a team of clinicians and administrative staff including GP&#39;s, Nurse practitioner, Clinical pharmacist, Healthcare assistants, Physician associates and Care navigators.You will be required to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide primary care nursing services including child immunisations, travel immunisations, cervical smears, wound management, diabetic review, contraception etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;provide timely clinical and culturally appropriate health services (educating patients re lifestyle, using recall and reminder systems etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;attending daily de-briefs, weekly clinical meetings, Monthly MDT meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain adequate levels of stock for materials, medication and equipment in all treatment and consulting rooms, ensuring no item is past its expiry date and that stock is rotated to minimise wastage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all patient consultations are recorded accurately in the clinical notes. This includes records of both face to face and remote conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
